	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes: you can find a billion examples and tutorials and books on how to learn C and do things in it, plus learn on a different platform (ex. present-day PCs).  This is not the case with 65xx assembly.  If you think this forum is equivalent (ed. how did my spell checker turn that into equivocal? Hahaha) to that, then you are wrong.<br /><br />I shouldn't even have to mention the learning curve of learning and working on a console -- in any PL.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
