	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />FYI, 0.9.5 added support for source-level debugging which lets you step through the original code, rather than just seeing the original code as comments like it did in previous versions (displaying the original code as comments is still supported though).  This also works with C projects, but it will work better with assembly projects (syntax highlighting, some minor issues, etc.): <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=215486#p215486">viewtopic.php?p=215486#p215486</a><!-- l --><br /><br />There's an option in the right-click context menu on the code that allows you to switch between disassembly &amp; source views (the option is only visible if a DBG file was loaded)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
